                <h3><i><b>Description About E-Commerce Website</b></i></h3>
                <br>
                <p>
                    An e-commerce website enables people to buy and sell physical goods, services, and digital products online instead of at a physical store. It allows businesses to process orders, accept payments, manage shipping and logistics, and provide customer service.
                <br>
                <p>
                    Commerce refers to the exchange of goods and services between two or more entities, typically involving buying and selling items of value. It can occur between businesses, between consumers, or between businesses and consumers.               
                 </p>
                <br>
                <p>
                    At its core, electronic commerce, or e-commerce, is the buying and selling of goods and services using the internet, as seen when shopping online. However, the term often encompasses all of a seller's efforts to sell products directly to consumers online.

                </p>
                <br>
                <p>
                    An eCommerce website allows visitors to find their product(s), add them to their “cart,” and securely enter their payment information to complete their purchase. Since the advent of credit card processing on the internet, eCommerce has permeated society and into our daily lives. With Covid and recent events, eCommerce has growth has exploded and is expected to hit $8.1 trillion in 2026 according to Shopify.
                </p>
                <br>
                <p>
                    What are the different types of eCommerce business models?
                    <ul>
                        <li>Business-to-business (B2B)</li>
                        <li>Business-to-consumer (B2C)</li>
                        <li>Consumer-to-consumer (C2C)</li>
                        <li>Consumer-to-business (C2B)</li>
                    </ul>
                </p>
                <br>
                <p>
                    What are the different types of eCommerce websites?
                    <ul>
                        <li>Single brand website</li>
                        <li>Online retailers</li>
                        <li>Affiliate websites</li>
                        <li>Marketplaces</li>
                    </ul>
                </p>
                <br>
                <p>
                    How do you make money with an eCommerce website?
